{"post_stream":{"posts":[{"id":3574600,"name":"Tom Winter","username":"tomjwinter","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/tomjwinter/{size}/110664_2.png","created_at":"2025-03-31T03:23:34.924Z","cooked":"<p>We had been having network issues at our last competition whenever our robot was rebooted, potentially related to Shuffleboard, so we made the switch to Elastic and are now having similar, but different issues. I tried to make it really simple and create a project with the just the following few lines of code and tried running it in my simulator (on a mac).</p>
<pre><code class="lang-auto">public class Robot extends TimedRobot {
  private SendableChooser&lt;String&gt; autoProgram;
  private static final String kOption1 = "Option1";
  private static final String kDoNothing = "Do Nothing";
  private static final String kDriveOut = "Drive Out";

  public Robot() {
    autoProgram = new SendableChooser&lt;&gt;();
    autoProgram.setDefaultOption("Option 1", kOption1);
    autoProgram.addOption("Do Nothing", kDoNothing);
    autoProgram.addOption("Drive Out", kDriveOut);
    SmartDashboard.putData("Auto Program", autoProgram);
  }
}
</code></pre>
<p>When the Elastic dashboard first connects to this code, the Combo Box chooser works great, but then if the robot code is stopped / restarted (without closing Elastic), the Elastic combos will display a red exclamation mark and it will never connect with the code (and autoProgram.getSelected() returns the wrong value) until I change the value in the dashboard, and then it syncs.</p>
<p>If I open AdvantageScope while the red exclamation mark is showing and connect to the Simulator, it shows the the “selected” entry for that ComboBox is blank, so it seems to be an issue with Elastic not reconnecting to the NetworkTables.</p>
<p>Is this normal?  Or am I missing some code that is needed to cause the elastic combo boxes to reconnect on code restart?</p>
<p>We have the newest WPILIB (2025.3.2) and had this same version for our last competition.</p>","post_number":1,"post_type":1,"posts_count":10,"updated_at":"2025-03-31T03:23:34.924Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":13,"reads":117,"readers_count":116,"score":88.4,"yours":false,"topic_id":497493,"topic_slug":"elastic-dashboard-sendablechooser-reconnect-issues","display_username":"Tom Winter","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"link_counts":[{"url":"https://www.chiefdelphi.com/t/elastic-2025-a-lot-of-little-things/472475/161","internal":true,"reflection":true,"title":"Elastic 2025: A Lot of Little Things","clicks":0}],"read":true,"user_title":"","bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":36869,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"post_url":"/t/elastic-dashboard-sendablechooser-reconnect-issues/497493/1","reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":true},{"id":3574616,"name":"Peter Johnson","username":"Peter_Johnson","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/peter_johnson/{size}/10417_2.png","created_at":"2025-03-31T03:41:29.982Z","cooked":"<p>There was an Elastic release today to fix this/similar issue.</p>
